Calling all new parents, soon to be parents, and parents with children up to age 18. @myparentmd is an incredibly useful resource in navigating the journey of parenthood. It’s a subscription based service that offers 24/7 access to a pediatrician, after hours nurses, and a community of caregivers. It is not meant to replace your child’s doctor- instead it is a supplement to ease the nerves and answer questions when unexpected situations come up. Use promo code CF15 for 15% off your subscription. Message me for more info!

“Oh say can you see, Mama! Oh say can you see!”
As a child, this is what I would yell any time I saw an American Flag. It was the symbol of my favorite song, The National Anthem. By age three, I had learned how to sing it by watching Rene Rancourt before @nhlbruins game. In high school, I would sing the national anthem then take the court as a player. I have always dreamt of singing that song at the Boston Garden, and last Friday, in front of 19,000 people, I got to make it a reality. Thank you @celtics @tdgarden for giving me a night I will never forget. I hope to do it again someday.

Ten years ago, with only a suitcase and a guitar, a kid from Massachusetts took a gigantic leap of faith with one goal in mind: a career in music. I slept on the floor of my house for the first three nights because I didn’t even have a bed. Since then, I’ve traveled all over the country, made more memories than I can remember, and checked a whole bunch off my bucket list. I got a dog, got married, had a baby girl. I’ve made new friends, lost some old ones, and learned more about myself than I ever could’ve had I never left. I wouldn’t be where I am or who I am without the people in these photos (sorry I couldn’t tag you all). Thank you all for joining me on this journey. Right after I moved, a close friend asked me, “How long we giving this?” Safe to say, we’re in it for the long haul. I can’t wait to see what the next ten years brings. Thank you Nashville 🙏🏼

So when @iga.obrycka reached out and said, “I need you for the grand opening of @barstoolnashville,” it was a no-brainer. For a kid from Boston to represent Barstool Sports in Nashville last night was a full circle moment and it did not disappoint one bit. Anybody know a good car accident attorney?

Yesterday, on her way home from work, Tracey was in a serious car accident. While traveling on 40E, traffic had stopped abruptly and a bucket truck didn’t stop in time, slamming into Tracey. She got crushed into the car in front of her and that car hit the car in front of it. All parties involved (except the truck driver) were taken to the hospital in an ambulance.

Tracey has suffered a fractured rib, fractured sternum, mild concussion, whiplash, and bruising all over. The vehicle did exactly what it was supposed to do - the front and back collapsed, but the frame stayed safe.

Tracey was able to walk away from the wreck and nobody was seriously injured or killed. It could‘ve ended much worse, and we are so thankful for that. In closing, wear your seatbelt. Always. You never know when it’ll save your life.
